text:
Dec 2024 update: Beef veg burger not as nice as fish veg burger.

Medium sized outlet with ample space to wait/walk around. Kiosk made ordering easy for working adults during lunch. Food was served fast. Seats were surprisingly available on weekday lunch.
The burger is a bit bland, nothing special. The self-ordering kiosk is very convenient. We ate here because it was raining outside.
Definitely our favorite place to go in Singapore. Best yakiniku fries!

Surprisingly crowded in the evening. Cramped seating arrangement. Fried chicken was burnt. Cappuccino, matcha latte, soup & strawberry bliss were ok.
A far cry from the MBFC Tower 3 days. Missed the sink for handwashing after meals.
Tried the rice burger infused with loval flavour. Like the sauce.
